definitions.definition: A Chinese divinatory text composed by the Confucian writer Yang Xiong (53 BCE-18 CE), similar to and inspired by the I Ching , and having 81 ternary tetragrams .

main_definition: A Chinese divinatory text composed by the Confucian writer Yang Xiong (53 BCE-18 CE), similar to and inspired by the I Ching , and having 81 ternary tetragrams .
